    public class TransitionNodeMaker<T,K>
extends AbstractNodeMaker
    Create a navigation Node corresponding to a transition Config properties (without navigation.prefix:
    • name.transition transition provider name (defaults to name).
    • name.key transition key to use (if unset look for IndexTransition).

    • Method Detail

      • makeNode

        public Node makeNode(java.lang.String name,
            FilteredProperties props)
        Description copied from interface: NodeMaker
        Create a Node for a named menu item. This is allowed to return null to indicate that nodes of this type are disabled/empty and should be suppressed. The NavigationMenuService can be configured to substitute a different node in this case (for example to host child nodes added by the configuration).

        Automatic child nodes can be added in this method and will appear first. Followed by nodes from the configuration then nodes from NodeMaker.addChildren(Node, String, FilteredProperties)

        Parameters:
        name - name of the node
        props - FilteredProperties containing the navigation menu configuration
        Returns:
        Node
